2. WORKFLOW NODE BREAKDOWN
==========================

Below is the technical breakdown of the nodes used in the n8n workflow, following the execution path from start to finish.

1. Manual Trigger (Workflow Start)

   * Function: Entry point of the automation. Executes the workflow when “Test Workflow” is clicked.
   * Purpose: Used for controlled batch execution during development or scheduled runs.

2. Workflow Configuration (Set Node)

   * Function: Initializes workflow variables and prepares configuration fields if needed.
   * Purpose: Acts as a setup layer before processing company data.

3. Google Sheets – Read Company Names

   * Function: Fetches company names from the input sheet.
   * Purpose: Serves as the primary data source for the workflow.
   * Input: Column containing company_name.

4. Split in Batches (Loop Over Companies)

   * Function: Processes one company at a time.
   * Purpose:

     * Prevents API rate limit issues
     * Improves stability
     * Ensures clean per-company processing
     * Enables scalable batch enrichment

5. AI Research Agent (LangChain Agent Node)

   * Function: Core intelligence layer of the system.
   * Behavior:

     * Accepts company name as input
     * Uses a strict system prompt enforcing JSON-only output
     * Searches and verifies publicly available data
     * Returns structured output

   Required JSON Schema:

   {
   "companyName": "string | null",
   "emailId": "string | null",
   "contactNumber": "string | null",
   "companyWebUrl": "string | null"
   }

   Guardrails Implemented:

   * No guessing allowed
   * Return null if unverifiable
   * Normalize phone numbers to international format
   * Prefer official corporate sources

6. OpenRouter Chat Model (AI Model Layer)

   * Model Used: google/gemini-2.5-flash-lite
   * Function: Executes the language model reasoning.
   * Purpose:

     * Performs contextual company research
     * Generates structured JSON output
     * Enables model flexibility via OpenRouter

7. Code in JavaScript (JSON Sanitizer & Validator)

   * Function: Post-processes AI output.
   * Responsibilities:

     * Removes markdown formatting (```json)
     * Safely parses JSON
     * Applies null fallback protection
     * Trims and normalizes fields
   * Purpose: Prevents workflow crashes from malformed AI responses.

8. Edit Fields (Field Mapper)

   * Function: Maps AI JSON fields to Google Sheet column schema.
   * Output Fields:

     * Company Name
     * Contact Number
     * Email ID
     * Company Web URL

9. Google Sheets – Append or Update

   * Function: Writes structured output into final sheet.
   * Mode: Append or Update (based on matching columns).
   * Purpose:

     * Maintains enriched dataset
     * Prevents duplicates
     * Creates structured company directory

10. Loop Continuation

* Function: Returns to Split in Batches node.
* Purpose: Continues processing next company until list is complete.

